{"lemma":"ساداتٌ","slug":"ساداتٌ","root":"س.#.د","root_slug":"س-_-د","root_link":"/words/roots/س-_-د","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun_prop","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَيِّد","root":"سود","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n18560","n21171","n21402","n21172","n21403","n21181","n21408","n21182"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D8%A7%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"master, lord, prince","examples":[{"text":"وَقَالُوا رَبَّنَا إِنَّا أَطَعْنَا سَادَتَنَا وَكُبَرَاءَنَا فَأَضَلُّونَا السَّبِيلَا","english":"Pickthall: And they say: Our Lord! Lo! we obeyed our princes and great men, and they misled us from the Way."},{"text":"هُنَالِكَ سَيِّدُونَ عَلَى الْبَسِيطَة\n تَائِهُون"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mister"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sir"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Sayyid (title of a male descendant of Mohammed)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"liberal, generous"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"noble, high-born"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"wise"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-Semitic *swd-. Cognate with Imperial Aramaic 𐡎𐡅𐡃 (swd), 𐡎𐡉𐡃 (syd, “to have lordship”)."},"ipa":["/saj.jid/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n18560","headword_ar":"سُيِدَ","root":"sA^d","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swd","text_ar":"سود"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21171","headword_ar":"سَيْدٌ","root":"swd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21402","headword_ar":"سَيْدٌ","root":"syd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v. in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swd","text_ar":"سود"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21172","headword_ar":"سِيدٌ","root":"swd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"syd","text_ar":"سيد"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21403","headword_ar":"سِيدٌ","root":"syd","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wolf:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, A, K: mentioned in the K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swd","text_ar":"سود"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and in the S, at the close of that art.:) accord. to Sb, its medial radical letter is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; its dim. being ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suyayodN","text_ar":"سُيَيْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": not like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of which the dim. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruwayoHapN","text_ar":"رُوَيْحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], nor like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"diymapN","text_ar":"دِيمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siydaAnapN","text_ar":"سِيدَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (K:) or so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siydaAnN","text_ar":"سِيدَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) which is the pl. (S, M, A) also: (M:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siydaAnapN","text_ar":"سِيدَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-wolf;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, and Ham p. 274;) [and] so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siydapN","text_ar":"سِيدَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ks, S;) or this is not allowable. (Ham ubi suprà.) One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siydu ramolK","text_ar":"سِيدُ رَمْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wolf of sands;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e., that frequents the sands; meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a savage wolf"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) Hence, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AimoraA^apN siydaAnapN","text_ar":"اِمْرَاَةٌ سِيدَانَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bold woman,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the she-wolf."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A lion"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K) is sometimes thus called, (S,) in the dial. of Hudheyl. (M.) The former is the primary signification accord. to J and others; though the contr. seems to be indicated in the K. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","A"]},{"entry_id":"n21181","headword_ar":"سَيِّدٌ","root":"swd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K, &c.,) of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawiydN","text_ar":"سَوِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for a reason to be mentioned below; the kesreh upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", being deemed difficult of pronunciation, is suppressed, and the quiescent"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus coming thgether, the latter receives the rejected kesreh, and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"is changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and incorporated into the augmentative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as in the case of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jay~idN","text_ar":"جَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with those who hold it to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawiydN","text_ar":"جَوِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] or, accord. to the Basrees, it is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEilN","text_ar":"فَيْعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayowidN","text_ar":"سَيْوِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] (S;) and also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayodN","text_ar":"سَيْدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mz, 40th"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nwE","text_ar":"نوع"},{"kind":"text","text":", section on the class of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hay~inN","text_ar":"هَيِّنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hayonN","text_ar":"هَيْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A chief, lord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, Mgh, Msb: [accord. to the last of which, this is a secondary signification, as will be seen below:])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a prince,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"king:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is set before,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"over, others: a master of a household:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a woman's husband:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, M, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a possessor, an owner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a proprietor:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"slave's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"owner:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, M, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a superior in rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"station"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition; one possessing pre-eminence"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excel-lence; a man of rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quality; a personage; a man of distinction:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who surpasses others in intelligence and property, and in repelling injury, and in beneficence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"usefulness, who makes a just use of his property, and aids others by himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one possessed of glory, honour, dignity, eminence, exalted"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elevated state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nobility;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, Msb; [accord. to the latter of which, this is the primary signification;])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous, noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high-born:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"most generous, noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high-born,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a people: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a liberal, bountiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"munificent, person:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clement; forbearing; one who endures injurious treatment from his people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devout, abstaining from unlawful things, and clement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbearing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Katádeh, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who is not overcome by his anger:"},{"kind":"text","text":"('Ikrimeh, L:) accord. to As, the Arabs say that it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any one who is subdued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repressed, by his principle of clemency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbearance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAy^idN","text_ar":"سَايِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one inferior to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~id","text_ar":"سَيِّد"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or, accord. to Fr, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA say~idu","text_ar":"هٰذَا سَيِّدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomihi Alyawoma","text_ar":"قَوْمِهِ اليَوْمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"this is the lord, &c., of his people today"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but if you announce that he will be their"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sy~d","text_ar":"سيّد"},{"kind":"text","text":"after a little while, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa saAy^idu qawomihi Eano","text_ar":"هُوَ سَايِدُ قَوْمِهِ عَنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaliylK","text_ar":"قَلِيلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idu","text_ar":"سَيِّدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) the fem. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAy^idN","text_ar":"سَايِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M, L, Msb:) pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAy^idN","text_ar":"سَايِدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAdapN","text_ar":"سَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayaAy^idu","text_ar":"سَيَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and [pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAdapN","text_ar":"سَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAdaAtN","text_ar":"سَادَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) [J says that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAdapN","text_ar":"سَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalapN","text_ar":"فَعَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [orinally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawadapN","text_ar":"سَوَدَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] because"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEiylN","text_ar":"فَعِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [as has been before mentioned;] and it is like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraApN","text_ar":"سَرَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariY~N","text_ar":"سَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", the only other instance"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1463},{"kind":"text","text":"of the kind; this being shown to be the case by the fact that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has also as a pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayaAy^idu","text_ar":"سَيَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", [and with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"because it is so changed in the sing.,] like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afiylN","text_ar":"اَفِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afaAy^ilu","text_ar":"اَفَايِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabiyEN","text_ar":"تَبِيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tabaAy^iEu","text_ar":"تَبَايِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but the Basrees, who hold"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fayoEilN","text_ar":"فَيْعِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", say that it becomes of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEalapN","text_ar":"فَعَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the pl. as though it were"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAy^idN","text_ar":"سَايِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAy^idN","text_ar":"قَايِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAdapN","text_ar":"قَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl., and like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAy^idN","text_ar":"ذَايِدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which has"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAdapN","text_ar":"ذَادَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a pl.; and they also say that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sayaAy^idu","text_ar":"سَيَايِدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idN","text_ar":"سَيِّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is contr. to analogy; for by rule it should be without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"'","text_ar":"ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  [In the present day it is also particularly applied to signify, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyf","text_ar":"شَرِيف"},{"kind":"text","text":", Any"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descendant of the Prophet."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-  One of the poets has used it in relation to the jinn, or genii; saying,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yanodubona say~idahun~apo \n                      \n                     \n                        jin~N hababona bilayolK"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Genii that were roused"},{"kind":"text","text":"from their sleep"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by night, summoning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or perhaps"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bewailing and eulogizing their chief"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: Akh says that this is a well-known verse of the poetry of the Arabs: but it is asserted by one, or more, likewise deserving of reliance, that it is of the poetry of El-Weleed [and therefore post-classical]. (M.) ―         -b4-  And the wild ass is called (assumed tropical:)  the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~id","text_ar":"سَيِّد"},{"kind":"text","text":"of his female. (TA.) ―         -b5-  Also, (Ks, S, M, Mgh, Msb, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siy~adN","text_ar":"سِيَّدٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) the latter on the authority of Aboo-'Alee, (TA,) applied to a he-goat, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Advanced in years:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, S, M; Mgh, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in its third year:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great,"},{"kind":"text","text":"though not advanced in years: (TA:) or it is of general application, for it occurs in a trad. applied to the camel and the ox-kind. (M, TA.) ―         -b6-  And the former also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What is most eminent, exalted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of any things: and is applied by Zj to the Kur-án, because, he says, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"say~idu AlkalaAmi","text_ar":"سَيِّدُ الكَلَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paragon of speech"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["Fr","L","M","Msb","ISh","K","S","Ks","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n21408","headword_ar":"سَيِّدٌ","root":"syd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siy~adN","text_ar":"سِيَّدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"swd","text_ar":"سود"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n21182","headword_ar":"سِيَّدٌ","root":"swd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the last sentence but one above."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}